The S&P 500, or simply the S&P, is a stock market index that measures the stock performance of 500 large companies listed on stock exchanges in the United States.
It is one of the most commonly followed equity indices.
Historical stock data for all current S&P 500 companies


You can get the dataset from Kaggle link below :
https://www.kaggle.com/camnugent/sandp500

I used a subset of that dataset the link to GitHub repo of which can be found on the same Kaggle dataset
I am attaching the link of that GitHub rep as well.
https://github.com/CNuge/kaggle-code/tree/master/stock_data

use individual_stocks_5yr.zip for the analysis
